Veterans of U.S. Flying Tigers visit memorial museum in Hunan
2015-09-06 00:35:29 GMT
Some veterans of the U.S. "Flying Tigers" air squadron and their relatives visited the Flying Tigers Memorial Museum in Zhijiang Saturday.The Flying Tigers, officially known as the American Volunteer Group of the Chinese Air Force, were formed in 1941 and led by U.S. General Claire Lee Chennault to help China drive out invading Japanese troops.
